= ABOUT =
php-restauth is a client library for the RestAuth protocol [1]. It provides an
interface for all features supported by the protocol. It exclusivly uses JSON as
data format. The library requires the pecl_http extension (see INSTALLATION).

Full API docs are available online at [2] or can be generated using the source
code (see Generating documentation).

[1] https://fs.fsinf.at/wiki/RestAuth
[2] https://fs.fsinf.at/doc/php-restauth

= INSTALLATION =
This library requires pecl_http [1]. You can install the library via PEAR using:
	pecl install pecl_http

Other than that this library should just be copied to a directory of your
choice. Creating a PEAR module for this is a TODO.

[1] http://php.net/manual/en/book.http.php

=== On Debian/Ubuntu ===
There is an APT repository providing debian packages for all restauth software.
Please see
	https://fs.fsinf.at/wiki/RestAuth/APT_repositories
for more information on how to add the repository to your system.

The packages for this library are called php-restauth and php-restauth-doc.

=== Generating documentation ===
Generating the documentation requires phpDocumentor[1]. If you have it
installed, you can generate documentation simply by running:
	make doc

[1] http://www.phpdoc.org/

= USAGE =
Please see examples/test.php for an extensive example script.

